FuncDef: The xml-translate end command translates configuration commands into XML packets in the NETCONF YANG model. The xml-translate end command translates configuration commands into XML packets in the NETCONF YANG model.
Examples: Warning: The running database will be locked when you enter the CLI-to-XML translate mode.Continue? [Y/N]:y
ExtraInfo: After the configuration commands to be translated are executed, to start the CLI-to-XML translation, run the xml-translate end command. The translation mode quits after the translation is complete.
